<div id="community-vibe">
    <h2 class="sect-title">Community Vibe in Elboya </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">The Elbow River park and pathway system is an excellent place for joggers and walkers,
                full of beautiful scenery and birdlife. </p>
            <p class="par-xl">Being a popular destination not just for the members of the adjacent communities, but also
                for all Calgarians. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Stanley Park borders Elboya to the north. With Elbow Drive and McLeod trail being the
                major transportation arteries, downtown is only a minute away, making easy convergence for those who
                work and enjoy the nightlife of the city core. 4th Street in Mission and 17th Avenue also are in close
                proximity, both being popular entertainment and shopping destination for Calgarians. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Restaurants in the area include Nellies Breakfast, Mercato Italian and Boston Pizza. The
                nightlife is booming with various bars and clubs, from The Ship & Anchor to Repulbik, it doesnâ€™t take
                long to find somewhere to have a good night.</p>

        </div>
